content.description: You get good gear on this and a fun squeeze to finish it off.
content.protection: #1-3, and you may want a 2nd #2. You need a very long slings/static to set up a TR on trees up top.
content.location: In the alcove on the right side of Phaeton Cliff, start on the right side of the alcove.

content.description: At the upper crag, climb up into the shallow cave along the really good flake to a pocket/hole. From the pocket/hole, the cracks turns to a seam then to a hand crack that takes a sharp right turn and turns into a good horizontal ledge/crack. Surmount the bulge, and gain the good, flat ledge in the corner at the end of the hand crack.
content.protection: Great gear: small and medium cams down low, a #2 or #1 works after the bulge, and a #3 works at the horizontal ledge.
content.location: About 12' left of Squeeze Chimney, find the OW with a hand crack that zags across to meet it about 20' up.

content.description: This is a broken, varied, solid cliff that is 30' is sections. Offwidths, hand cracks, flakes, roofs, there is lots of potential.
